I'm sure people have said this before, but Pok√©mon should really listen to this. An open world Pokemon game on today and next gen consoles would be an absolute killing for the company. Ive been a loyal fan since Red/Blue as a kid, and still play today. But to introduce a new concept on to these new systems, will the graphics that can be produced. I could only image what it would feel like to battle Brock in Pewter City Gym for his badge with my Charmander. Allowing us to fully explore every corner of the Kanto region, and as bad as this sounds, I know Pokemon wants to make money, release DLC such as Johto, Hoenn, etc...I personally would be the first to buy a season pass for this. 7 generations of pokemon would be phenomenal. All I'm saying is consider it. The Pokemon generation is alive and well, Pokemon Go proved that. Give us a console version game and watch your numbers skyrocket! Just don't limit the game to nintendo only, let xbox and PS have a crack at these gems you can produce!

Why would they let x box or ps have a chance? That's literally stupid for them money wise. If its exclusive to their systems then you have to buy Nintendo games platforms etc. If the others have it also then they lose money because a lot of people will buy them for other systems.

One of the problems I always see with the open-world idea is scaling. In HG/SS, the EXP gained from each fight was reduced. If we had 7 regions, for it to remain equally difficult at all times the EXP gain would be really, REALLY small.  If it stayed normal, you'd be overpowered before you reach Hoenn. If it was like an MMORPG and levels were capped for each gym, it'd be pretty annoying for players. And if you start over each time you go to a new region, you may as well be playing the original games.

Also the Nintendo only aspect is simply for profit. Microsoft and Sony would end up taking 30% or more (at a guess). Exclusives tend to be less unfair for developers. 

Additionally if they DID do this, they'd be setting the bar stupidly high. Where do they go from there? A one region game? Who cares, the last one had 7! Everything would just be DLC at that point.

Not to mention that Pok√©mon already IS open-world, just with 1-2 regions.

Anyway, that's an indie dev's opinion on why this would never happen. Sure it's a player's dream but it won't happen.
